# Rule 010 - Planning Sync

## Session start

1. Read `.planning/STATE.md` - section "Current Position" and "Session Continuity".
2. Read `.planning/.bootstrap.json`.
3. Do NOT read `.planning/PROJECT.md` or `.planning/ROADMAP.md` unless the task explicitly requires them.

## Session end

Update `.planning/STATE.md`:

- "Last session" -> today (YYYY-MM-DD).
- "Stopped at" -> the last task finished or point of hand-off.
- "Next 3 TODOs" -> concrete next actions.
- "Current owner" -> clear if you were the owner.

Do NOT rewrite sections that did not change. The file stays short on purpose.

## Diff discipline

When you need to sync with changes, use `git diff --stat` first. Only read the full diff of files that matter to the current task. This saves tokens and avoids context drift.

## When to update ROADMAP.md

Only when an ADR justifies it. Tactical changes live in STATE.md.
